`docs/` is the project's rationale and status layer for the ctx system — an LLM code-context-generation tool. Nothing here is executable; it's the record an engineer reads before touching the codebase to understand why things are the way they are and what's currently unfinished.

DECISIONS.md is append-only history (ADRs), STATUS.md is the live task queue, and DYLINT_RULES.md is a spec for lint rules not yet built. STATUS.md and DYLINT_RULES.md both reference mechanical stand-ins that exist today (scripts/rationale_check.py, scripts/cycle_check.sh) as partial/temporary substitutes for future enforcement — changes to those scripts should be reflected in both docs. STATUS.md is itself generated output (`ctx-context .`) and points back to DECISIONS.md for rationale, so STATUS.md should never contain "why," only "what's outstanding."

Invariant: at MVP, none of the nine dylint rules are enforced — only rule 1's line-count check has any live mechanical equivalent. Anyone adding real dylint enforcement must update both DYLINT_RULES.md's status and STATUS.md's task list.

No intent.md exists for this directory, so no divergence check applies.